params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.key
params.description: [Output Only] A key that provides more detail on the warning being returned. For example, for warnings where there are no results in a list request for a particular zone, this key might be scope and the key value might be the zone name. Other examples might be a key indicating a deprecated resource and a suggested replacement, or a warning about invalid network settings (for example, if an instance attempts to perform IP forwarding but is not enabled for IP forwarding).

params.name: data.value
params.description: [Output Only] A warning data value corresponding to the key.
